    // Landing page content
    landingBadge: "Sport Science · TKD Specific",
    landingHeroTitle: "Strength & Conditioning for",
    landingHeroHighlight: "Taekwondo Athletes",
    landingHeroDesc: "Sport science-based S&C programs built around your kick performance, competition calendar, and injury history.",
    psSectionLead: "Built for the sport. By people who train it.",
    psWhoTitle: "Who it's for",
    psWhoBody: "Taekwondo athletes, coaches, and clubs who take performance seriously — from competitive juniors building their base to seniors chasing podiums.",
    psProblemTitle: "The problem",
    psProblemBody: "Generic training apps don't understand taekwondo. Coaches juggle spreadsheets, athletes guess at periodization, and progress lives in scattered notebooks.",
    psSolutionTitle: "The solution",
    psSolutionBody: "One platform built for TKD: periodized training, mental performance, nutrition, rehab, and physical testing — connecting athletes and coaches in one place.",
    landingWhatTitle: "What Is Sportstalent?",
    landingWhatP1: "Sportstalent is a strength and conditioning platform built exclusively for taekwondo athletes. Unlike generic fitness apps, every training plan is rooted in taekwondo sport science — periodized programming that develops explosive power, rotational speed, and reactive agility without compromising flexibility or adding unnecessary muscle mass.",
    landingWhatP2: "The platform generates individualized weekly training plans based on your athlete profile: belt level, weight class, competition calendar, training frequency, injury history, and specific goals. Whether you're preparing for a national championship or building a general strength foundation as a color belt, the program adapts to your exact situation.",
    landingWhatP3: "Each plan follows established periodization principles — moving through anatomical adaptation, maximum strength, power conversion, and competition peaking phases. This isn't random exercise selection. It's structured programming designed by sport scientists who understand the biomechanical demands of turning kicks, spinning techniques, and 3-round sparring matches.",
    landingWhoTitle: "Who Is It For?",
    landingWhoIntro: "Sportstalent is designed for competitive taekwondo athletes training 4–6 times per week who need structured strength and conditioning work alongside their dojang sessions. The platform serves:",
    landingWhoItem1: "Competitive sparring athletes (cadet to senior) preparing for national and international tournaments",
    landingWhoItem2: "Poomsae athletes who need precision, balance, and controlled power output",
    landingWhoItem3: "Coaches managing multiple athletes who need individualized S&C programs at scale",
    landingWhoItem4: "Junior athletes (U15–U21) building foundational strength without inappropriate loading",
    landingWhoItem5: "Athletes returning from injury who need progressive, sport-specific rehabilitation programming",
    landingWhatYouGetTitle: "What You Get",
    landingBenefit1: "Programs auto-adjust to your belt level, weight class, and competition calendar",
    landingBenefit2: "Every exercise includes a 'Why for TKD' explanation — no generic gym work",
    landingBenefit3: "Periodized across preparation, competition, and transition phases",
    landingBenefit4: "Tracks volume, intensity, and fatigue to prevent overtraining",
    landingBenefit5: "Integrates with your dojang schedule — never conflicts with TKD sessions",
    landingBenefit6: "Includes injury prevention protocols for ankles, knees, and hips",
    landingProofAthletes: "50+ athletes",
    landingProofJump: "10.5% avg jump increase",
    landingProofLevel: "Cadet → Senior level",
    landingValuePeriodizedTitle: "Periodized Programming",
    landingValuePeriodizedDesc: "Structured phases from anatomical adaptation through competition peaking — not random workouts.",
    landingValueSportTitle: "TKD-Specific Exercises",
    landingValueSportDesc: "Every exercise has a 'Why for TKD' explanation. No generic gym programming.",
    landingValueAITitle: "Personalized Plans",
    landingValueAIDesc: "Individualized programs based on your belt level, weight class, and competition calendar.",
