    privacyPolicyTitle: "Privacy Policy",
    privacyDraftBanner: "⚠️ DRAFT — pending legal review. This privacy policy has not yet been finally approved by a data protection advisor and is not binding in its current form.",
    privacyLastUpdated: "Last updated",
    privacyVersion: "Version 0.1 — draft",
    privacyWhoWeAre: "Who we are",
    privacyWhoWeAreDesc: "Sportstalent.dk (CVR 33685815), contact rashid3105@gmail.com, operates this platform. For the website, user accounts and payment, Sportstalent is the data controller. For athletes' training and health information, the individual club is the data controller and Sportstalent acts as a data processor on the club's behalf under a data processing agreement.",
    privacyWhatWeCollect: "What information we process",
    privacyCollect1: "Contact information: name, email, club, role, date of birth/age.",
    privacyCollect2: "Sensitive health information (GDPR art. 9): resting heart rate, heart rate variability (HRV), sleep, steps, weight, food logs, supplements, injury descriptions, mental assessments and readiness check-ins.",
    privacyCollect3: "Training data: plans, logs, competitions, evaluations, reflections and diary.",
    privacyCollect4: "Communication and parent information: messages between coach and athlete, comments, as well as the parent's email and consent for minors.",
    privacyCollect5: "Technical data: usage analytics via Microsoft Clarity as well as device and login information.",
    privacyWhyWeCollect: "Purposes and legal basis",
    privacyPurpose1: "Delivery of the platform's functionality — legal basis: performance of a contract (art. 6(1)(b)).",
    privacyPurpose2: "Processing of health information — legal basis: explicit consent (art. 9(2)(a)). For athletes under 18, parental consent is obtained.",
    privacyPurpose3: "Operation, security and improvement of the service — legal basis: legitimate interest (art. 6(1)(f)).",
    privacyLegalBasis: "Legal basis",
    privacyLegalBasisDesc: "Where we process sensitive health information, it is done solely on the basis of explicit consent. Consent can be withdrawn at any time, after which processing ceases. For minors under 18, consent is obtained from a parent or legal guardian.",
    privacyDataSharing: "Data sharing and processors",
    privacyDataSharingDesc: "We only share information with processors that handle data on our behalf under a data processing agreement: Supabase (hosting and database, EU region), Simply.com (email delivery), Microsoft Clarity (anonymised usage analytics) and Anthropic (AI text generation, see below). We never sell your information.",
    privacyAiTitle: "AI-assisted content generation",
    privacyAiDesc: "To generate training plans, rehab suggestions and analyses we use an AI service from Anthropic (Claude). The information sent for processing is not used to train Anthropic's models. The processing may involve transfer of information to the United States; the transfer takes place on the basis of the European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC). [To be confirmed against Anthropic's data processing agreement.]",
    privacyHosting: "Hosting and data location",
    privacyHostingDesc: "Our database and hosting are provided by Supabase with a data centre in the EU/EEA. Data at rest and in transit is protected, and access is restricted per club via Row Level Security.",
    privacyMinorConsent: "Consent for minors",
    privacyMinorConsentDesc: "Athletes under 18 are only processed with consent from a parent or legal guardian. Consent is obtained via a confirmation link sent to the parent's email before health data is processed. Adult athletes (18+) give their own consent in the app. Consent can always be withdrawn.",
    privacyRetention: "Retention",
    privacyRetentionDesc: "We retain information for as long as the account is active. When you delete your account, your personal data is permanently removed, and information included in shared features (e.g. message threads) is anonymised. Specific retention periods are determined together with the club as data controller.",
    privacyYourRights: "Your rights",
    privacyRight1: "Access to the information we process about you.",
    privacyRight2: "Rectification of incorrect information.",
    privacyRight3: "Erasure of your information ('the right to be forgotten').",
    privacyRight4: "Data portability — export of your data in a machine-readable format.",
    privacyRight5: "Withdrawal of consent as well as objection to and restriction of processing.",
    privacyRightsHow: "You can exercise your rights in the app (export and account deletion) or by contacting us. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Danish Data Protection Agency (datatilsynet.dk).",
    privacyCookies: "Cookies",
    privacyCookiesDesc: "We use necessary cookies for login and operation as well as Microsoft Clarity for anonymised usage analytics. We do not use cookies for advertising.",
    privacyContact: "Contact",
    privacyContactDesc: "If you have questions about the processing of your information or wish to exercise your rights, you can contact us at:",
