    changelogEntry85: "Post-competition reflection is easier to find — you'll get a Home-page prompt for up to 14 days after an event, and the Past competitions list moves to the top of the Competitions page whenever something needs reflection.",
    changelog_2026_04_26: "April 26, 2026",
    changelogEntry86: "1–10 performance rating in post-competition reflection — the AI now sets concrete SMART goals anchored to your lowest scores so the next plan targets your real weak points.",
    changelogEntry87: "Compact \"Create athlete\" — the button in the coach dashboard is now an icon-and-modal, so the header no longer wraps on mobile; the athlete limit (e.g. 3/5) is shown inside the dialog itself.",
    changelogEntry88: "System cleanup & stability — removed unused components, hooks, and a failing edge function; switched edge functions to esm.sh imports for more reliable deploys.",
    changelog_2026_04_27: "April 27, 2026",
    changelogEntry89: "Wearables sync (Apple Health & Health Connect) — read-only pull of sleep, resting heart rate, HRV, steps, and workouts. A new Recovery tile appears on your dashboard and your morning Readiness check-in auto-fills from last night's data. Coaches see a 7-day recovery sparkline per athlete.",
    changelogEntry90: "Friendlier dashboard welcome — replaced the experience/sessions/program stats with your Next upcoming competition or camp and a Daily quote of the day in 6 languages.",
    changelogEntry91: "Wearables Help section + connection status — clear platform-specific setup steps in Help, plus a green pulsing \"Connected\" indicator and a dedicated Sync status page (last pull, sample count, errors) on the Wearables screen.",
