    helpParentPortalTitle: "Parent/Guardian Portal",
    helpParentPortalSteps: "Give a parent or guardian secure, permanent read-only access to your training overview.\n\n1. Go to your Profile settings.\n2. Scroll to 'Parent Access' (only visible for under-18 athletes).\n3. Tap 'Generate invite link' and share it via copy, WhatsApp, or email.\n4. The parent clicks the link, creates an account (or logs in), and confirms the link.\n5. They are redirected to the Parent Dashboard — a clean view showing your active training plan schedule, competition results, and session attendance.\n6. Diary entries and mental assessments are never shown to parents.\n7. To remove access, go back to 'Parent Access' in your profile and tap 'Remove access'.",
    changelog_2026_05_12: "May 12, 2026",
    changelogEntry111: "Injury rehab is now available to everyone on the Athlete plan",
    changelog_2026_05_11: "May 11, 2026",
    changelogEntry110: "Weekly squad PDF export now includes an AI-written summary per athlete — based on diary entries, readiness check-ins, and training completion — written in the coach's language and ready to share with the athlete",
    weeklyReportGenerating: "Generating AI summaries… this may take a moment",
    weeklyReportNoData: "Insufficient data to generate a summary this week.",
    weeklyAthleteReport: "Weekly Athlete Report",
    weeklyReportFooter: "Generated by Sportstalent.dk · Coach-only document",
    helpWeeklyReportTitle: "AI Weekly Athlete Report",
    helpWeeklyReportSteps: "Generate a weekly PDF report for all your athletes with an AI-written summary per athlete that can be shared directly.\n\n1. Go to your Coach Dashboard.\n2. Tap 'Export Squad PDF' in the squad overview.\n3. The app fetches each athlete's diary entries, readiness check-ins, and workout completion for the current week.\n4. An AI summary is generated per athlete in your app language — warm, direct, and written to the athlete in second person.\n5. The PDF downloads automatically with one section per athlete: weekly schedule, training overview, and AI summary.\n6. The footer notes 'Coach-only document' — remind athletes this is a coaching tool if you share it.",
    helpRolesTitle: "Roles",
    helpRolesSteps: "A user can have the role Athlete, Coach, or both.\n\n1. The role is set when your account is created and can be changed in your profile settings.\n2. The app interface and color theme automatically adapt to your active role.\n3. Athletes see a training-focused dashboard with next session, stats, diary and quick access buttons.\n4. Coaches see a squad overview with athlete counts, inactive alerts, team stats and coaching tools.",
    helpRoleSwitcherTitle: "Switch Role",
    helpRoleSwitcherSteps: "If you have both roles, a pill-toggle appears at the top of the home screen.\n\n1. Tap 'Athlete' or 'Coach' to switch between views.\n2. Your choice is saved to your profile and remembered for your next login.\n3. The color theme changes instantly: blue accent for athlete mode, orange accent for coach mode.\n4. All dashboards, navigation and features update to match your selected role.",
    changelog_2026_05_10b: "May 10, 2026",
    changelogEntry109: "Built-in Beep Test timer with automatic audio beeps, level progression, and direct save to athlete profiles — available for both coaches and individual athletes",
    beepTestTitle: "Beep Test Timer",
    beepTestStart: "Start Test",
    beepTestCountdown: "Get ready…",
    beepTestLevel: "Level",
