    beepTestSelectAthlete: "Select athlete for this test",
    beepTestSelectAthletes: "Select athletes",
    beepTestSelectAll: "Select all",
    beepTestDeselectAll: "Deselect all",
    beepTestSelected: "selected",
    beepTestEndAll: "End test for all",
    beepTestNotSaved: "Not saved",
    ptEditResult: "Edit result",
    helpMatchReportTitle: "AI Match Report & PDF",
    helpMatchReportSteps: "Generate a detailed WT-rules based performance report from any tagged video and download it as a PDF.\n\n1. Open a match video with at least 3 tags.\n2. Tap 'Generate Match Report' below the tag list.\n3. The AI analyses your tags against World Taekwondo rules — kyorugi or poomsae — and generates a structured report.\n4. For poomsae, select the sub-type (Individual / Pair / Team) and optionally enter the athlete's age when uploading the video. The analysis applies the correct WT judging criteria.\n5. For kyorugi, the age determines the ruleset: Cadet (≤13, no head turning kicks), Junior (14–17), or Senior (18+).\n6. The PDF downloads automatically with sections for Summary, Strengths & Weaknesses, Technical Analysis, Training Recommendations, and Tactical Notes.",
    helpChatTitle: "In-app Chat",
    helpChatSteps: "Send messages to coaches, teammates and parents directly in the app.\n\n1. Athletes: tap the chat bubble button at the bottom of the screen. Coaches: tap the Messages button on the Coach Dashboard (it opens a dedicated page at /coach/messages).\n2. Tap + to start a new direct message — search for a name and tap to open.\n3. Coaches can tap the group icon to create a group conversation and add members including parents (shown with (P)).\n4. Long-press any message to add an emoji reaction.\n5. Tap the microphone icon to dictate a message — it transcribes automatically.\n6. Swipe or hover a conversation to archive it.\n7. Tap ⋯ on your own message to edit or delete it.\n8. In direct messages, a small avatar shows when the other person has read your message.\n9. Enable push notifications in your Profile to get alerts when new messages arrive.",
    changelog_2026_05_04: "May 4, 2026",
    changelogEntry95: "HIIT module in the Library: 6 Taekwondo-specific interval workouts (Tabata Kicks, Olympic Blitz, Sparring Rounds and more) with a full-screen interval runner, audio cues, haptic feedback and circular progress timer.",
    changelogEntry96: "Fresh, sporty palette across the entire app — unified light theme with electric blue and lime accents replacing the dark cockpit, so public and authenticated pages now feel like one product.",
    changelogEntry97: "New club-focused landing page at sportstalent.dk with a streamlined Athlete / Coach / Small Team flow and a compact \"What's new\" teaser linking into the changelog.",

